I REALLY wanted to like this place, especially because it’s a black owned business in brooklyn, and every time I see it on Caviar I want to order.  Visited yesterday and ordered two drinks with some fries (because of Cuomo’s new regulation) while we waited for our friends to join us.  Frozen watermelon/tequila drink was great, so were the fries.  When our friends joined we ordered the fried calamari/fish/shrimp, the broccoli, a lobster club w/fries, and two crab cakes and some more drinks.  When our food arrived they had forgotten the lobster club (my meal) entirely so I had to run back in and alert them, no big deal.  Tried to the broccoli while I waited for my food and it was just bland, and one of our friends complained the whiting tasted overly fishy, which is usually a sign of the fish not being as fresh as could be.  The server sent out my lobster club and this time I noticed the fries which were really good earlier were now severely undercooked. So I politely let them know and they took the meal away and returned it back to me 5 minutes later with fully cooked fries (albeit not seasoned as well as our first serving - rushing).  I bit into my sandwich and realized there was no bacon.  So again I headed back indoors to say hey, my club has no bacon, no need to remake it, please just send out some bacon.  I got bacon that was both really chewy and burnt in other sections, so my guess is it was made earlier in the day and reheated.  The lobster club itself had a few pieces of lobster shell inside of it so I couldn’t even finish the sandwich.  I just picked the lobster out and tossed the sandwich.  The drinks were good though and outside of the fishy whiting and my meal just getting mangled everyone was having a good time so we ordered a 3rd round of drinks which had been delicious up until this point.  This round the frozen drinks had clearly sold through well and this batch was clearly not ready.  The drinks arrived watery and melted into a syrupy elixir in a few minutes.  Look, any kitchen could have a bad day or mess up a meal, but this is quality control.  How do you even get shell pieces into a lobster roll? That has NEVER happened to me before.  I REALLY REALLY wanted to like this place, but I’ll need to stick to CrabbyShack when I’m in the neighborhood and looking for seafood.  This place ain’t it.

I’ve been to this specific restaurant numerous times and had exceptional service but during this visit when I try to treat  my family from North Carolina, Pennsylvania to some of what I would call great food the customer service was horrible! My reservation for the 8 of us was for 5 pm there was no problem there, sat took our order and that’s where the confusion came. Major of the orders were incorrect and my son didn’t receive his meal til 20minutes after everyone at the table has finished their plates. No one checked in on us and as far as extra napkins, condiments I had to get up to retrieve everything. When we received our bill it was additional$ 70 higher than expected because many things were on our bill that wasn’t ordered and on top of that someone else’s bill was still in the book. Being that me and my sister treated our family of 8 we split it! We both signed off on our split bill. But I was charged for my half and an additional bill that was enclosed in book. If I didn’t check my account I was would have been pay for numerous bills. After speaking to management I was told that it was swiped twice because it didn’t go through the first time. How so if it was two different price charges?? He ensured me the balance would be dissmissed after 3-5 days but I get another alert two days later and the original split was charged to my card again!!! Are you serious... this is the biggest inconvenience I have ever experienced in any restaurant... now I have to spend more time on the phone with a manager trying to sort out why my card was charge and additional change!!!

This place is great!  My companion and I decided to drive to Brooklyn one Saturday night and explore dining options. I checked Google Maps for an area that had a decent amount of dining options. I’d never heard of Peaches before, but the name intrigued us. We walked down a few mostly residential blocks and came upon a quaint, lively restaurant with a small crowd standing out front. I just had brunch at this establishment, The Absolute Worst! My fiance and I have a tradition to have brunch every Sunday and today we chose this establishment. Our serve for today was a young lady by the name of Lea D. She's a pretty dark shin African-American woman with a low cut caesar much like myself. So for starters I ordered the Brioche Toast with a Brownstone Punch, and he ordered the Brooklyn Wings. For our main brunch entree, I had the whole lump crab cake Benedict, and my fiance had the Long Island Whiting Sandwich with a side of Sauteed Kale. Well shortly after putting our order in that when everything went haywire. A four-top sat down not too long after we put our order in. First I had to get up out my seat and go find Lea D to request another drink. Next, the four top that was seated after us food came out first and two of them had ordered the steak and eggs. At that time Lea D was just bringing me the drink that I had to go and ask her for. I asked Lea D what exactly happened to the order of food that we had placed before the four top, she responded and said: ” I will go and check”.  Well, she left and never came back, no seriously she never came back. One of the food runners brought us our food and Lea D was nowhere around. I checked my food before the food runner left and guess what!!!! I didn't even have the whole lump crab cake and my fiance didn't receive his sauteed kale. Well, I went and asked to speak to the manager. I didn't manage to get his name but he was very nice and he also took off our brunch entrees. The madness didn't stop there, Lea D never returned to check on our table and she had her other co-workers doing her job. The food was decent, the service was great- the server was really kind and polite. The inside was insanely noisy, so we sat outside in complete darkness, no candles or lights, at least it was quiet. A little too romantic, no? They did give candles to the inside tables, which made no sense.  Grilled Octopus ($14)- 5/5 This had white beans, kale and salsa verde as the sauce and was surprisingly good. The kale added a nice texture to it, and I thought the sauce was kind of basic but ended up pairing quite well with the octopus.  Blue crab spaghetti ($18)- 3/5 I don't understand the rave for this popular dish. It was very basic pasta to me. It wasn't bad, but I wasn't blown away by it. There was a good amount of crab in it at least.  Low Country Seafood Boils Snow Crab Legs ($20)- 3/5 This was good, but a lot of effort needed just for tiny pieces of crab meat. The best part was probably the corn which was delicious and well marinated, although quite small... Potatoes were good too, so was the dipping sauce it came with. The gloves had a strong latex smell, the cracker for the snow crab leg also had a metal taste/smell. But the price for this was decent.

I would probably try again because the food was really good but service left something to be desired. Hopefully it would be better the next time.
